To launch GAMGI from panel:

On GNOME:
1) Right click on panel and choose: Add to Panel,
then choose on new dialog: Custom Application Launcher
2) Fill properties:
Type: Application
Name: GAMGI
Command: gamgi
Comment: Build, View and Analyse Atomic Structures
3) Press on icon and choose gamgi32.png

On KDE:
1) Right click on panel and choose: Add Application to Panel, Add Non-KDE application
2) Fill properties:
Button title: GAMGI
Description: Build, View and Analyse Atomic Structures
Executable: gamgi
3) Press on icon and choose gamgi32.png
